    'subtitle3' => 'Transparency by design',

    'text1' => '
    <ul>
        <li>Big Tech companies collect your browsing habits, app usage, location history, and even voice data — often without clear consent.</li>
        <li>Internet providers (ISPs) log your connections, visited domains, and traffic metadata — because it’s profitable and legal in many places.</li>
        <li>Your data is monetized: used for targeted advertising, profiling, political influence, or training AI models.</li>
        <li>Smaller, shady companies simply sell raw user data to brokers — your online life becomes a product.</li>
        <li>Free VPNs are never free — they survive by harvesting and selling your activity, sometimes even injecting ads or malware.</li>
    </ul>',

    'text2' => '
    <ul>
        <li><em>Encrypted traffic</em> — your ISP or mobile provider can’t log or monetize your online activity.</li>
        <li><em>Secure DNS</em> — prevents providers and intermediaries from seeing which sites you visit.</li>
        <li><i>Masking your IP address</i> — websites and trackers see only our exit nodes, not your real location.</li>
        <li><em>Censorship bypass</em> — access blocked resources freely and securely.</li>
        <li><i>Crypto-only payments</i> — no banks,   no payment processors, no personal identifiers.</li>
    </ul>',

    'text3' => 'Tuneliqa runs only on open-source protocols and clients. No black boxes. No trackers. All code is auditable.',
);
